bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Vice President for Student and Academic Support Services of The George Washington University reports to the President. The office oversees a wide range of areas related to student life: Admissions (undergraduate), Athletics and Recreation, Financial Assistance, Dean of Students, Career Center, Community Living and Learning Center, University Counseling Center, International Services, Marvin Center, Mount Vernon Campus Life Office, Multicultural Student Services Center, Office of Community Service, Parent Services, Presidential Administrative Fellowship, Recreational Sports and Fitness Services, SASS Communication and Technology, Student Activities Center, Student Health Services, Summer Camp: The GW Summer Tour, Student Judicial Service, Colonial Inauguration, Disability Support Service, Center for Alcohol and other Drug Education, and University Police.
In 2003 the name was changed to Senior Vice President for Student and Academic Support Services. Before 1989 it was named Vice President for Student Affairs.
N.B. This history note was written in 2005

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include publications, committee files, ledgers, pamphlets, and posters. They range in date from circa 1821 to 2005, and were transferred to the University Archives by the Vice President for Student and Academic Support Services.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into ten series: Records, Office files, Office files, Student Club Cooperative Store [Student Union], Scrapbook, Communication, Communication, University counseling center, Communication and Creative Services, and Student Activities Center.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains programs, flyers, brochures, maps, correspondence, invitations, schedules, reports, memorandums, handbooks, guides, minutes, applications, publications, a survey, newsletters, rosters, and calendars. They range in date from approximately 1821 to 2005. The materials concern student orientation, information for parents, recreational activities, Recreational Sports and Fitness services, job descriptions, the Five-to-One Program, residence assistants, handicapped awareness programs, regulatory procedures for student life, campus unity, student regulations, student's rights, student responsibilities, honor constitutions, "Inertia", career conferences, financial aid, activities books, Parent's Day, Family Week, Parent's Week, May Day activities, "The GWU Money Manual", student life, open houses, the Student Activities Center, leisure guides, student activities on campus, blood drives, skills for living series, policies and procedures for student activities, Welcome Week, orientation, the Presidential Administrative Fellows Program, "The Campus Calendar", "This Month in Washington D.C.", "This Week at GWU", annual report of the Student Activities Office, student organizations, the Student Council, Student Health Services, transfer students, information for freshmen, event calendars, academic calendars, alumni calendars, GW administrative responses to student protests, the Maury Hall takeover, "The Cox Commission Report and George Washington University", anti-war strikes, the Office of Safety and Security, identification cards, Colonial Express Shuttle Bus, 4-Ride Escort Service, the University Police Department, "Security Blanket", campus security, study abroad, "GW Abroad", the International Student Society, international student advising, "Greek Wire", rosters of student organizations, the Office of Greek Affairs, Colonial Inauguration (student orientation), and faculty advisors.

The information includes materials and publications produced from the Student Activities Office; the International Services Office; Office of Public Relations; Office of Parent Services; The George Washington University Parents' Association; the Office of the Dean of Students; the University Activities Office; the Office of Campus Life; the Student Affairs Office; Disabled Student Services; the Office of Student and Academic Support Services Communication and Technology; the Student Placement Office; the Student Financial Aid Office; the Dean of Summer Sessions; the Office of Greek Affairs, and the Student Activities and Organizations Office.
Additionally, a book of the minutes of the Student Council for the Class of 1921 officers is included.
Formerly vertical files.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains photographs of students, parents, families and events including meetings of the Parents Association Advisory Council, Colonial Inauguration (CI), move-in, and family weekend. DVD recordings of Colonial Inauguration (1991, 1993, 1995-2002, 2009-2011). Copies of the Colonial Parents' Connection newsletter (1993-2002). Parents' Association branded weekly planners (2009). Also included one copy of the 2011 Cherry Tree.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some of the photographs bear copyright notices by local photographers hired by GWU.
